## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the reliance on secondary sources. The economic impact of overfishing can vary significantly by region, and localized studies may provide more detailed insights. Additionally, the complexity of global seafood markets and the interplay of various economic factors mean that the full economic impact of overfishing may not be fully captured in this report. Further research, including primary data collection and analysis, would be beneficial to gain a more comprehensive understanding of the issue.